race.comment: CABRINELLA (1) hasn't been all that far away in her two runs this time in work, the latest in a BM65 over this distance at the Sunshine Coast. Didn't have the best luck in running that day so the effort was full of merit. Very fit now and this is a huge drop in class. Clear top pick. MHASAHN (5) won first-up at Kilcoy then showed pace but was swamped late over 800m at Warwick last time out. Will appreciate a little less pressure up front today and from a good draw is going to be hard to reel in. KIRONA STORM (6) was far too good for a Tabulam maiden field over this trip three weeks ago. Took a while to break the ice but can go on with it now. WENDT (7) was beaten just 1.4 lengths in a BM58 here at this distance two back. Definite contender fresh from a 46-day let-up. BELLZEN (2) is first-up. Boasts good form last prep in better races than this. Must be included.
